org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.fxg.dom.types

Enum BlendMode

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<BlendMode>
      • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.fxg.dom.types.BlendMode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<BlendMode>

    public enum BlendMode
extends Enum<BlendMode>
    The BlendMode enumeration determines which blend mode to use when compositing with the background. The ordinal for the enumeration is significant for the following BlendModes supported in FXGVersion.v1_0 as it matches the SWF specification for the BlendMode property of the PlaceObject3 tag. 
       0 = normal
   1 = normal
   2 = layer
   3 = multiply
   4 = screen
   5 = lighten
   6 = darken
   7 = difference
   8 = add
   9 = subtract
  10 = invert
  11 = alpha
  12 = erase
  13 = overlay
  14 = hardlight
    The following Blendmodes were introduced in FXGVersion 2.0. Their implementation needs PixelBurst support. 
        colordodge
    colorburn
    exclusion
    softlight
    hue
    saturation
    color
    luminosity
    The following was introduced in FXG 2.0 which acts like blendMode="layer" except when alpha is 0 or 1, in which case it acts like blendMode="normal" 
                    auto
